On Tuesday, you can ride the Purple Line Express from Howard to Linden at about 3:15. Then the Holiday Train turns around and heads to the Loop for it last ride downtown for the season. Pick up the Purple Line Express in the Loop at 4:38 p.m., and ride it back north. <a href="http://www.transitchicago.com/travel_information/holidaysched/20151216.aspx" target="_blank">Check out</a> the complete schedule.

And Wednesday is the last day to catch the Holiday Train, leaving from Howard at 3:05 p.m. It keeps shuttling to and fro from Howard to Dempster in Skokie until the last departure at about 7:20 from Dempster. <a href="http://www.transitchicago.com/travel_information/holidaysched/20151223.aspx" target="_blank">View</a> the full schedule.

Wednesday also is the date for the last run of the Holiday Bus. It departs 79th/Western at 12:30 p.m. going north as the #49 Western.

You can get photos with Santa on the Holiday Bus from about 4:30 to 5:30 p.m. at 79th/Western.

